<div class="blue-background">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4 well signin">
			<h4>Forgot your password?</h4>
			<p>Submit your email address and weâ€™ll send you a link to reset your password.</p>

			<%= simple_form_for(resource, as: resource_name, url: password_path(resource_name), html: { method: :post }) do |f| %>
			  <%= f.error_notification %>

			  <div class="form-inputs">
			    <%= f.input :email, required: true, autofocus: true %>
			  </div>

			  <div class="form-actions">
			    <%= f.button :submit, "Submit", class: "btn-primary btn-block btn-lg" %>
			  </div>
			<% end %>

		
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 shared">
			<p>Psst ... If it's any help, Minibarra requires that passwords be at least 8 characters long and does not require you to include numbers or uppercase letters. If that jogs your memory, <a href="/users/sign_in" style="text-decoration: underline">try signing in again.</a></p>
			<div class="padding">
				
			</div>
		</div>
		
	</div>
</div>